content:
Highlight Externally Visible Feed Items in Case Feed

You can mark feed items in the case feed that are visible to external users. This way support agents can easily distinguish between feed items that are visible to your customers and ones that are visible only to internal users, like support agents.

Available in: Salesforce Classic (not available in all orgs)
Available in: Enterprise, Performance, Unlimited, and Developer Editions

User permissions needed:
Manage Cases
Customize Application

By default, the case feed doesnâ€™t distinguish feed items according to who can see them. To mark this distinction, enable both the Highlight Externally Visible Feed Items and Enable Experience Case Feed settings.

To mark your case feed items:

Enable the Highlight Externally Visible Feed Items setting.
Select the feed-based page layout that you want to edit, click Edit.
Scroll to the Feed View settings and select Highlight Externally Visible Feed Items.
Enable the Enable Experience Case Feed setting.
Enter Support Settings in the Quick Find box and click Service | Support Settings.
Select Enable Experience Case Feed.
title: Highlighting External Feed Items in Salesforce
